Multi-stage phishing sometimes starts with a harmless-looking email asking the user to call a number, moving the exploit into voice where security controls are scarcer and confidence easier to manufacture.
Secrets accidentally committed to Git repositories can persist in history even after deletion, which is why scanning and key rotation usually matter more than a hopeful force-push.
