Parameter pollution and parser discrepancies matter because security checks often happen in one layer while business logic lives in another, and software does not always agree on what the request means.
Post-exploitation often includes querying security products, backup software and remote-management tools first, because understanding the defender’s estate is just sensible if you plan to ruin it methodically.
