Cross-origin resource sharing misconfigurations can expose APIs if origins are trusted too broadly, because “allow all” remains a depressingly popular substitute for design.
Adversaries sometimes use cloud-hosted virtual desktops as staging environments, blending operations into mainstream providers and forcing defenders to tell normal from abnormal in very familiar places.
